World number one Novak Djokovic has said that in order for him to progress to the Japan Open semi-final, he played like a machine. "I am not a machine. But I did play like one today. This was one of the best matches I played this year," he said. "I am very, very pleased with the way I feel and played on the court." The Serb, 32, took 50 minutes to beat world number 24 Lucas Pouille 6-1 6-2.  Djokovic is competing at his first tournament since he withdrew from the US Open in September with a shoulder injury. Djokovic, will face either David Goffin of Belgium or Chung Hyeon of South Korea in the semi-finals.